PlQIXUO7Vn2tLYWfXAUON0mnAVD4sn-HkrIzH2W8l8ccq4s=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying method calls**\\n\\nI'm realizing that the extension is a static method call to the extension method, not using Select on qual. I'm trying to think through evalApply2 with funSym flags; it might relate to Module or perhaps a module method? It seems I'm ruling out Helper. \\n\\nNow, can a class extend Integer? No, it's final. And Long is also final. I’m questioning if a custom class can be `isInstanceOf[java.lang.Integer]` via value class, but that doesn't seem possible.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "No test changes were made.\n\nI analyzed `NameMapper.scala` for the active class:\n\n`CompileTimeEval$QuoteScope$HelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCall`\n\nThe helper path is only constructed by the library’s compile-time evaluator for numeric `+` on boxed `java.lang.Integer` or `java.lang.Long` values:\n\n```scala\nHelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCall(x, x, \"sum\", args)\n```\n\nThat then calls:\n\n```scala\nhelperObj.getClass().getMethod(name, argsTypes: _*)\nmethod.invoke(helperObj, nArgs: _*)\n```\n\nHowever, `argsTypes` are derived via `arg.getClass`, so for `Int + Int` the lookup becomes:\n\n```java\nInteger.class.getMethod(\"sum\", Integer.class, Integer.class)\n```\n\nThe JDK exposes `Integer.sum(int, int)`, not `Integer.sum(Integer, Integer)`, so the lookup cannot succeed through the normal public jsoniter-scala macro API. Consequently, the later `Method#invoke` call site is not reachable through supported behavior in this artifact.\n\nCovering it would require either:\n\n- asserting this broken numeric compile-time-evaluation path,\n- directly instantiating private/internal macro helper classes,\n- using direct reflection against internals, or\n- shadowing/modifying JDK/library classes,\n\nall of which violate the task rules.\n\nI also did not run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c2f353477ff5f86016a1157b26944819f8