] || x.isInstanceOf[java.lang.Long]) {\n    HelperObjectJvmReflectionMethodCall(x, x, \"sum\", args)\n  }\n```\n\nThat helper prepends the boxed receiver and derives argument types from runtime classes:\n\n```scala\nval nArgs = prependArgument(obj, args)\nval argsTypes = retrieveArgTypes(nArgs)\nhelperObj.getClass().getMethod(\"sum\", argsTypes: _*)\n```\n\nFor `Int + Int`, this attempts:\n\n```java\nInteger.class.getMethod(\"sum\", Integer.class, Integer.class)\n```\n\nFor `Long + Long`, this attempts:\n\n```java\nLong.class.getMethod(\"sum\", Long.class, Long.class)\n```\n\nBut the JDK exposes:\n\n```java\nInteger.sum(int, int)\nLong.sum(long, long)\n```\n\n`Class#getMethod` does not perform boxing/unboxing during lookup, so the reflective lookup fails before reaching `Method#invoke`.\n\nCovering both remaining call sites would require one of the disallowed approaches:\n\n- asserting the broken numeric compile-time-evaluation path,\n- directly invoking private/internal macro helper classes,\n- using reflection in the test to reach internals,\n- shadowing or replacing JDK/library classes.\n\nPer the task rule, because this path is only reachable through behavior that is broken in this artifact version, I left the call sites uncovered rather than adding a misleading or rule-violating test.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c2f353477ff5f86016a115889f17c819f91553eadc9e7b918\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 12230, "output": 883, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 44857, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1779521663237, "responseId": "resp_0c2f353477ff5f86016a1158808a5c819fa8debbb1eca5a373"}}
